  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "The requirement of originality in copyright law underscores the necessity for human input in works claiming copyright protection.",
    "This human-centered approach remains pivotal in assessing AI-generated and AI-assisted creations, especially in multimodal contexts like video game design, where various media such as text, audio, and visuals are integrated.",
    "Historically, originality is tied to human creativity, as highlighted in cases like Allen v. U.S.",
    "Copyright Office, where the court deemed that human prompts were insufficient for copyright eligibility without substantial creative involvement from a human (Dai & Jin, 2023).",
    "This ruling reflects the emphasis placed on direct human authorship within copyright law, challenging the applicability of copyright to fully AI-generated works, especially those that lack significant human intervention."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "Copyright Office, where the court deemed that human prompts were insufficient for copyright eligibility without substantial creative involvement from a human (Dai & Jin, 2023)."
  ]
}